-- Brazil's inflation rises 5.91 pct in 2013, tops forecasts
-- 
-- Fri Jan 10, 2014 06:05AM EST
-- None



RIO DE JANEIRO, Jan 10 (Reuters) - Brazil's benchmark IPCA consumer price index <BRCPIY=ECI> rose 5.91 percent in the 12 months through December, accelerating from its 5.77 percent increase posted through the prior month, government statistics agency IBGE said on Friday.

The central bank targets inflation at 4.5 percent, with a tolerance margin of 2 percentage points. On a monthly basis, the IPCA index <BRCPI=ECI> rose 0.92 percent from November, above the 0.82 percent median forecast of 28 economists. Below is the result for each price category:  DecemberNovember  - Food and beverages  0.890.56  - Housing 0.520.69  - Household articles  0.890.38  - Apparel 0.800.85  - Transport   1.850.36  - Health and personal care0.410.41  - Personal expenses   1.000.87  - Education   0.050.08  - Communication   0.740.40